Vulnerability Explanation
1️⃣ Weak Credentials

Test credentials were left active in FTP.

2️⃣ Credential Reuse

Same credentials worked for SSH service.

3️⃣ Hidden Service (Security by Obscurity)

SSH was running on non-standard port 7223.

4️⃣ Sudo Misconfiguration

User allowed to run /usr/bin/vim as root without password.

This falls under:

Broken Access Control
OWASP Top 10 – A01

Impact

• Full system compromise
• User data exposure
• Root-level access achieved
• Misconfiguration allowed total takeover

Mitigation

• Disable anonymous FTP
• Enforce strong password policies
• Avoid credential reuse
• Remove unnecessary sudo privileges
• Do not allow editors like vim in sudo without restriction
• Restrict SSH to standard port with firewall rules

